AC
!AC
K
!K
p(AC|K)=1,~p(AC|!K)=1/m,~ p(K)=p
p(K|AC)=\frac{p(AC|K)p(K)}{p(AC)}
p(K|AC)=\frac{p}{p(AC)}
p(AC)=p(AC|!K)p(!K)+p(AC|K)p(K)
p(AC)=(1/m)(1-p)+1* p
p(K|AC)=\frac{p}{(1/m)(1-p)+ p}
p=\frac{1}{2}
m=3
p(K|AC)=\frac{\frac{1}{2}}{\frac{1}{3}\frac{1}{2}+\frac{1}{2}}=\frac{\frac{1}{2}}{\frac{1}{6}+\frac{1}{2}}=\frac{3}{4}
m=5
\frac{5}{6}
